The paper deals with wireless communication networks and beamforming techniques, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the coordination and cooperation between multiple base stations, which falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel technique for beamforming in the vertical plane, which is related to Multimedia (cs.MM) and Computer Engineering (cs.CE) sub-categories.
